uploader: Jazz at Lincoln Center's JAZZ ACADEMY
title: Tips on Auditioning for a Jazz Conservatory
description:
Students: learn the music ahead of time, master the melody, and practice the blues!

Master saxophonist Gary Bartz, also professor at Oberlin Conservatory, talks about what he is looking and listening for when students audition for him.

Learn more by visiting the Jazz Academy at http://academy.jazz.org

Gary Bartz - Instructor
Eric Suquet - Director
Bill Thomas - Director of Photography
Aaron Chandler - Sound Engineer
Seton Hawkins - Producer
fulltitle: Tips on Auditioning for a Jazz Conservatory
channel: Jazz at Lincoln Center's JAZZ ACADEMY
